This roll is based on triton's chemistry roll.

URL="http://git.rocksclusters.org/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi?p=triton/chemistry/.git;a=snapshot;h=604b04ef86a148ab8ab053f80de4ee38468c2ddb;sf=tgz"
wget $URL -O chemistry.tar.gz

ROLLCOMPILER, ROLLNETWORK and ROLLMPI variables are set in Makefile.
To overwrite run: 
    make ROLLCOMPILER=gnu ROLLMPI=openmpi ROLLNETWORK=mx
Produces a roll with a name that begins "namd_gcc_mx_openmpi" 

From original roll README:

This roll source supports building with different compilers and for different
network fabrics and mpi flavors.  By default, it builds using the gnu compilers
for openmpi ethernet.  To build for a different configuration, use the
ROLLCOMPILER, ROLLMPI and ROLLNETWORK make variables, e.g.,

    # make ROLLCOMPILER=intel ROLLMPI=mpich2 ROLLNETWORK=mx 

The build process currently supports one or more of the values for the variables:
ROLLCOMPILER: gnu, intel, pgi  (default gnu)
ROLLMPI     : openmpi, mpich2,and mvapich2 (default openmpi)  
ROLLNETWORK : any variable value(s) to load appropriate mpi modules, assuming 
              that there are modules named $(ROLLMPI)_$(ROLLNETWORK) available 
              (e.g., openmpi_ib, mpich2_mx, etc.).

